Implementation for issue 04 (Verification Gate + Fix Loop + Command Deny-list) is complete:

- **`src/ai_factory/safety.py`** ‚Äî new Command Deny-list module (`check_command` ‚Üí `DeniedCommandError` on match).
- **`src/ai_factory/verify.py`** ‚Äî new Verification Gate module; deny-checks all commands *before* executing any, runs in `install‚Üílint‚Üítypecheck‚Üítest‚Üíbuild` order, stops at first failure, `degraded=True` when no commands exist.
- **`src/ai_factory/runner.py`** ‚Äî rewired to run the gate after `implement`, then a bounded Fix Loop (default 2 attempts) re-invoking a `fix` phase on failure, producing `implemented_verified` / `implemented_degraded` / `implemented_unverified` / refusal on a deny-listed command.
- **`src/ai_factory/report.py`** ‚Äî now shows factory-verified Verification Gate results and Fix Loop attempts distinctly from agent-claimed summaries.
- **`src/ai_factory/presets/fake_agent.py`** ‚Äî Fake Agent now has deterministic `fix`-phase behavior so Fix Loop success/exhaustion scenarios are constructible with plain Makefile fixtures.
- Tests added: `tests/test_safety.py`, `tests/test_verify.py`, `tests/test_verification_gate_fix_loop.py`.

